-- World Bank Considers $200 Million Contingency Loan for Uruguay
-- B y   L u c i a   B a l d o m i r
-- 2012-05-31T19:26:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/world-bank-considers-200-million-contingency-loan-for-uruguay.html
The  World Bank  is considering
granting a $200 million contingency loan to Uruguay, the
lender’s representative in the South American country said.  “The loan will be reviewed by the board in October,”
Peter Siegenthaler told journalists in Montevideo today.  In 2011, the bank gave Uruguay a $260 million dollar
contingency loan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Baldomir in Montevideo at 
 lbaldomir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
